1
00:00:05,801 --> 00:00:07,431
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,501 --> 00:00:09,171
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,801 --> 00:00:13,171
This is a product from the factory
we contracted with,

4
00:00:13,241 --> 00:00:14,371
made for another brand.

5
00:00:14,441 --> 00:00:15,771
The quality is pretty good,
isn't it?

6
00:00:16,411 --> 00:00:17,941
The stitching and finish are clean,
right?

7
00:00:18,541 --> 00:00:19,541
They are.

8
00:00:19,611 --> 00:00:22,811
The factory's pretty big
and well equipped too.

9
00:00:23,711 --> 00:00:25,581
Ju Ah, behind you!

10
00:00:30,051 --> 00:00:31,091
CEO Gong?

11
00:00:32,721 --> 00:00:33,721
Yes.

12
00:00:34,591 --> 00:00:35,891
Yes, I'm sorry. Well...

13
00:00:36,591 --> 00:00:39,331
It's not bad.
The stitching is consistent, too.

14
00:00:40,731 --> 00:00:42,701
CEO Gong and I will...

15
00:00:42,771 --> 00:00:45,231
negotiate quantity
and unit price with the factory.

16
00:00:45,501 --> 00:00:48,671
Oh, right. You said you have
a meeting with Catch and Top today?

17
00:00:48,971 --> 00:00:51,871
Yes. If today's meeting goes well
and we secure a spot in their store,

18
00:00:51,971 --> 00:00:53,941
it'll open the way for us
to attract investors.

19
00:00:54,881 --> 00:00:56,611
It's such a huge online store,

20
00:00:57,251 --> 00:01:00,151
I don't know if a startup like us
can even get our foot in the door.

21
00:01:00,251 --> 00:01:01,821
Just trust me and CEO Gong.

22
00:01:02,651 --> 00:01:03,891
Shouldn't I go to the meeting
with you?

23
00:01:04,191 --> 00:01:05,761
- No.
- But,

24
00:01:06,061 --> 00:01:09,361
for a company like Catch and Top,
things will go more smoothly if I...

25
00:01:13,401 --> 00:01:15,831
Oh my, I'm sorry. Are you okay?

26
00:01:16,731 --> 00:01:18,401
Oh, yes. I'm fine.

27
00:01:23,671 --> 00:01:24,811
Mun Sik.

28
00:01:25,811 --> 00:01:26,811
Mi Hyang.

29
00:01:27,711 --> 00:01:28,981
Mun Sik.

30
00:01:29,681 --> 00:01:33,021
- How have you been?
- How have I been?

31
00:01:33,751 --> 00:01:36,051
I've been going through all this
just to see you.

32
00:01:36,651 --> 00:01:39,021
Jo Mi Hyang spotted.

33
00:01:39,091 --> 00:01:41,991
All units, Saenara Road.
Converge on Alley 38.

34
00:01:42,261 --> 00:01:45,831
Sir, we'll be there any second.
Please buy us some time.

35
00:01:46,201 --> 00:01:50,131
- I'm sorry. I had no choice.
- Mun Sik.

36
00:01:54,271 --> 00:01:58,941
- Did you get my letter?
- Yes. Don't worry.

37
00:01:59,711 --> 00:02:02,511
I don't trust anyone but you.

38
00:02:03,881 --> 00:02:05,381
As it should be.

39
00:02:13,391 --> 00:02:15,361
We've arrived at 38 Saenara Road.

40
00:02:36,351 --> 00:02:37,481
Here. This way.

41
00:02:42,851 --> 00:02:45,351
- Is this place abandoned?
- No.

42
00:02:45,991 --> 00:02:48,091
An elderly woman
with poor mobility lives here alone.

43
00:02:50,791 --> 00:02:53,161
I was wondering why
the police couldn't find you.

44
00:02:53,231 --> 00:02:55,131
You were hiding
right under their noses.

45
00:02:55,671 --> 00:02:58,631
I know this neighborhood
better than they do.

46
00:02:58,941 --> 00:03:00,141
Don't worry.

47
00:03:00,641 --> 00:03:02,201
We'll hide here until dawn,

48
00:03:02,271 --> 00:03:04,571
then go board the cargo ship.
All right?

49
00:03:05,211 --> 00:03:06,211
Yes.

50
00:03:06,711 --> 00:03:08,811
By the way,
why did you run away last time?

51
00:03:09,211 --> 00:03:11,081
You messed everything up.

52
00:03:11,281 --> 00:03:13,881
Hey, it's because
you were struggling so much.

53
00:03:13,951 --> 00:03:15,951
I was going to turn myself in alone.

54
00:03:16,021 --> 00:03:17,451
Don't sound so weak.

55
00:03:18,391 --> 00:03:20,121
If we successfully stow away,

56
00:03:20,391 --> 00:03:22,161
we won't have to live
in hiding anymore.

57
00:03:22,731 --> 00:03:24,291
Right. I'm sorry.

58
00:03:24,731 --> 00:03:25,731
Have a seat.

59
00:03:29,931 --> 00:03:34,001
Your memory still hasn't
completely returned, has it?

60
00:03:34,201 --> 00:03:35,201
Right.

61
00:03:36,071 --> 00:03:37,811
What did you say
your name was again?

62
00:03:38,111 --> 00:03:40,911
My name? It's Jo Mun Sik.

63
00:03:41,711 --> 00:03:44,751
Then who did I kill?

64
00:03:44,851 --> 00:03:47,251
Gosh, why do you want to know?

65
00:03:47,881 --> 00:03:50,021
You'll only feel worse
if you find out.

66
00:03:50,391 --> 00:03:54,621
The police kept asking,
so it made me curious.

67
00:03:54,821 --> 00:03:56,761
Who did I kill?

68
00:04:00,931 --> 00:04:02,131
Gong Gi Cheol.

69
00:04:04,731 --> 00:04:06,801
The person you killed...

70
00:04:07,101 --> 00:04:08,701
was Gong Gi Cheol.

71
00:04:09,671 --> 00:04:11,171
I see...

72
00:04:12,781 --> 00:04:15,481
But how did I injure my head?
I went to the barbershop,

73
00:04:15,541 --> 00:04:18,381
- and they said I have a scar.
- I told you already.

74
00:04:18,611 --> 00:04:22,081
I must've forgotten.
Will you tell me again?

75
00:04:26,091 --> 00:04:27,791
When you were standing on the chair,

76
00:04:28,321 --> 00:04:31,391
- I pushed you off.
- You did? Why?

77
00:04:31,561 --> 00:04:34,331
You said you were tired of me.
You asked how long...

78
00:04:34,331 --> 00:04:36,531
I was going to live like that
and told me to get my act together.

79
00:04:38,271 --> 00:04:41,901
You called me a parasite.

80
00:04:41,971 --> 00:04:44,671
- So I did.
- You did.

81
00:04:45,911 --> 00:04:47,711
So in a fit of rage, I pushed you.

82
00:04:48,381 --> 00:04:52,521
You slammed your head on the corner
of the furniture and didn't get up.

83
00:04:52,881 --> 00:04:53,881
And then?

84
00:04:54,321 --> 00:04:56,851
So I called the hospital.

85
00:04:57,691 --> 00:05:00,391
The only doctor there who made
house calls was Gong Gi Cheol.

86
00:05:00,861 --> 00:05:01,991
That man...

87
00:05:02,461 --> 00:05:04,891
was the kindest one
in the neighborhood.

88
00:05:05,531 --> 00:05:07,101
His wife, too.

89
00:05:12,871 --> 00:05:15,701
- You're here, Dr. Gong?
- Yes. Where's the patient?

90
00:05:15,771 --> 00:05:16,911
In that room. Hurry.

91
00:05:17,011 --> 00:05:19,081
My brother was changing
a light bulb,

92
00:05:19,141 --> 00:05:20,511
and he fell off a chair.

93
00:05:21,011 --> 00:05:23,281
He hit his head hard
on the corner of the furniture.

94
00:05:23,351 --> 00:05:24,481
Is he unconscious?

95
00:05:25,151 --> 00:05:26,981
He won't wake up
no matter how much I shake him.

96
00:05:27,051 --> 00:05:29,551
Then you should've called
911 immediately.

97
00:05:29,621 --> 00:05:34,061
We don't have money for the ER.
Please, save him, Dr. Gong.

98
00:05:59,551 --> 00:06:02,551
What's wrong, Dr. Gong?

99
00:06:03,751 --> 00:06:05,861
He's already deceased.

100
00:06:06,121 --> 00:06:10,431
No. That can't be.
Please, check again, Dr. Gong.

101
00:06:10,491 --> 00:06:13,261
There's no pulse
and he's not breathing.

102
00:06:13,331 --> 00:06:15,261
There's no pupillary
response either.

103
00:06:15,531 --> 00:06:17,801
No!

104
00:06:19,741 --> 00:06:22,841
My brother wouldn't die
and leave me all alone.

105
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:27,881
Hurry up and do something.
Save him. You're a doctor.

106
00:06:27,941 --> 00:06:32,781
I'm sorry.
He's beyond any help I can offer.

107
00:06:33,051 --> 00:06:34,781
We have to report this
to the police first.

108
00:06:34,851 --> 00:06:37,691
No. He's not dead.
My brother is not dead, I tell you.

109
00:06:37,751 --> 00:06:40,691
Let go of me. Please, calm down.

110
00:06:40,761 --> 00:06:44,961
- Bring him back!
- We have to call the police first.

111
00:06:45,031 --> 00:06:48,231
No. He's not dead.
He's not dead yet.

112
00:07:13,991 --> 00:07:15,191
So then...

113
00:07:16,191 --> 00:07:19,361
- I killed Gong Gi Cheol?
- Yes.

114
00:07:20,131 --> 00:07:22,571
No, you suddenly woke up,

115
00:07:22,571 --> 00:07:25,941
and smashed Gong Gi Cheol
over the head with a rock.

116
00:07:26,601 --> 00:07:28,171
I didn't even have a chance
to stop you.

117
00:07:28,941 --> 00:07:31,541
- So, what happened next?
- Next...

118
00:07:32,011 --> 00:07:34,911
You said your head hurt
and fell asleep.

119
00:07:35,441 --> 00:07:39,081
So I buried Gong Gi Cheol's body
in the mountains all by myself.

120
00:07:39,621 --> 00:07:40,951
I see.

121
00:07:41,581 --> 00:07:45,851
But by the time I got back,

122
00:07:46,221 --> 00:07:49,861
you were asking,
"Who are you? Where am I?"

123
00:07:52,161 --> 00:07:54,331
You'd lost your memory.

124
00:08:01,371 --> 00:08:03,571
You don't actually believe that,
do you?

125
00:08:04,411 --> 00:08:05,471
What did you say?

126
00:08:06,011 --> 00:08:07,241
Murderer.

127
00:08:08,781 --> 00:08:11,051
- Mun Sik.
- Why would I be your brother?

128
00:08:12,281 --> 00:08:13,751
My gosh.

129
00:08:14,051 --> 00:08:16,651
They must've fed you
some weird medicine.

130
00:08:17,251 --> 00:08:18,791
Mun Sik, get a grip.

131
00:08:19,151 --> 00:08:21,891
- Get a grip, Jo Mun Sik.
- My name is Gong Gi Cheol.

132
00:08:21,961 --> 00:08:25,961
- You're Jo Mun Sik.
- Mun Sik was dead when I arrived.

133
00:08:26,131 --> 00:08:28,401
And you're the one who hit me
over the head with that rock.

134
00:08:28,531 --> 00:08:32,031
No way. Your memory's back?

135
00:08:32,101 --> 00:08:36,741
Yes. How could you do this? How?

136
00:08:37,911 --> 00:08:39,341
So what if I did?

137
00:08:39,981 --> 00:08:43,711
- Statute of Limitations has run.
- The Statute of Limitations?

138
00:08:43,781 --> 00:08:45,251
That's right, you fool.

139
00:08:45,311 --> 00:08:47,721
The Statute of Limitations
for imprisoning me,

140
00:08:47,781 --> 00:08:50,221
abusing me,
and stealing 30 years of my life...

141
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:54,061
- hasn't run out.
- Then just kill me.

142
00:08:54,691 --> 00:08:55,991
Instead of rotting in prison,

143
00:08:56,531 --> 00:08:58,761
let's just end it all here,
you and me. All right?

144
00:08:58,761 --> 00:09:01,101
Just kill me!

145
00:09:01,161 --> 00:09:02,161
No.

146
00:09:02,671 --> 00:09:03,771
I'm going to live.

147
00:09:04,331 --> 00:09:07,001
I'm going to live happily
for the rest of my life.

148
00:09:08,401 --> 00:09:12,541
Don't be ridiculous.
Who do you think will believe you?

149
00:09:12,611 --> 00:09:15,011
You're a fool
who can't remember a thing.

150
00:09:16,251 --> 00:09:20,051
- They may not believe me, but you.
- What?

151
00:09:20,121 --> 00:09:22,321
I have the confession. Move in now.

152
00:09:22,381 --> 00:09:25,791
What? I thought you threw those out.
What is this?

153
00:09:27,091 --> 00:09:28,921
- Is it recording clearly?
- Yes.

154
00:09:29,461 --> 00:09:31,061
Wait, but...

155
00:09:31,531 --> 00:09:34,801
- Can you give me one more mic?
- Pardon?

156
00:09:34,861 --> 00:09:38,171
She's incredibly sharp.
She'll notice this.

157
00:09:39,131 --> 00:09:40,141
Let's do that.

158
00:09:40,701 --> 00:09:43,371
- Yes. Then one more on the inside.
- Right.

159
00:09:43,611 --> 00:09:46,381
What? Oh my.

160
00:09:46,981 --> 00:09:50,511
Oh my, what's this?
This isn't what it looks like.

161
00:09:50,581 --> 00:09:52,311
- What is this?
- Jo Mi Hyang, you're arrested...

162
00:09:52,311 --> 00:09:54,321
for attempted murder
and false imprisonment.

163
00:09:54,951 --> 00:09:59,761
What? Don't tell me you tricked me.

164
00:09:59,991 --> 00:10:01,861
I took care of you for 30 years.

165
00:10:02,161 --> 00:10:04,931
And you're so ungrateful.
How could you do this to me? How?

166
00:10:04,991 --> 00:10:05,991
Grateful?

167
00:10:06,331 --> 00:10:08,631
I'm the one who lost 30 years
because of you.

168
00:10:09,031 --> 00:10:11,201
I lost my family because of you.

169
00:10:11,271 --> 00:10:14,071
- I'm your family.
- You're not my family.

170
00:10:14,371 --> 00:10:18,011
What? Wait. No. You.

171
00:10:18,511 --> 00:10:21,311
You're mine.
You were my dead brother's...

172
00:10:21,381 --> 00:10:23,651
gift to me.

173
00:10:23,881 --> 00:10:28,151
Jo Mun Sik. Mun Sik!

174
00:10:28,151 --> 00:10:30,721
- Mun Sik!
- You did a great job.

175
00:10:32,591 --> 00:10:33,721
Are you okay?

176
00:10:37,131 --> 00:10:41,661
Oh, yes, I understand. Thank you.

177
00:10:42,461 --> 00:10:43,801
Hey, what did they say?

178
00:10:43,871 --> 00:10:46,301
Did they catch Jo Mi Hyang?
Is Gi Cheol okay?

179
00:10:46,371 --> 00:10:50,671
Yes, Father caught her himself
and he's fine.

180
00:10:54,611 --> 00:10:56,711
It's all over now, Mother.

181
00:10:57,981 --> 00:10:58,981
Good.

182
00:10:59,681 --> 00:11:00,681
Good.

183
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:08,861
- Father.
- Father. Are you okay?

184
00:11:08,991 --> 00:11:11,991
- Are you hurt?
- No, I'm perfectly fine.

185
00:11:12,061 --> 00:11:14,731
Mr. Gong caught her himself.

186
00:11:14,801 --> 00:11:17,501
- He got a full confession from her.
- He did?

187
00:11:17,571 --> 00:11:20,371
Father, why would you do something
so dangerous?

188
00:11:20,671 --> 00:11:24,441
Well, I was curious about
what really happened.

189
00:11:24,711 --> 00:11:26,981
But the moment I heard
Jo Mi Hyang's story,

190
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:28,541
some of my memory came back.

191
00:11:30,281 --> 00:11:31,951
Father, you got your memory back?

192
00:11:32,481 --> 00:11:34,121
Not all of it, just a little.

193
00:11:34,481 --> 00:11:35,481
Really?

194
00:11:37,191 --> 00:11:39,791
- Oh, thank you. Thank you so much.
- Don't mention it.

195
00:11:39,891 --> 00:11:41,961
I'm so relieved, Father.

196
00:11:49,471 --> 00:11:50,771
It really is.

197
00:12:06,381 --> 00:12:07,951
I'm home.

198
00:12:08,921 --> 00:12:10,021
Welcome home.

199
00:12:10,651 --> 00:12:12,021
I was waiting for you.

200
00:12:12,551 --> 00:12:14,921
I'm sorry for making you wait
so long.

201
00:12:16,631 --> 00:12:17,791
It's okay.

202
00:12:18,331 --> 00:12:20,801
I'm just glad you're back safe.

203
00:12:23,601 --> 00:12:25,001
- Let's go in.
- Okay.

204
00:12:25,071 --> 00:12:26,071
Yes, Father.

205
00:12:35,081 --> 00:12:36,081
She startled me.

206
00:12:36,281 --> 00:12:39,281
(Cabinetry Factory)

207
00:12:40,621 --> 00:12:42,921
CEO Gong, don't tell me
you have PTSD...

208
00:12:42,991 --> 00:12:44,691
from what happened yesterday.

209
00:12:45,521 --> 00:12:47,991
It's just a temporary
stress reaction.

210
00:12:50,331 --> 00:12:53,101
I wonder if you'll even be able
to handle the meeting today.

211
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,531
I'm going to handle it perfectly,

212
00:12:55,601 --> 00:12:57,731
so you can save
your needless worrying.

213
00:12:58,771 --> 00:12:59,771
Right.

214
00:13:01,671 --> 00:13:04,841
If you're worried, just say so.
Stop pretending you're not.

215
00:13:05,011 --> 00:13:07,111
Who says I'm worried?

216
00:13:07,681 --> 00:13:10,651
You came rushing over,
worried something had happened.

217
00:13:11,151 --> 00:13:12,151
Ju Ah!

218
00:13:17,151 --> 00:13:18,351
- Ju Ah.
- Come on,

219
00:13:18,451 --> 00:13:20,291
that woman was lunging at you
with a hammer.

220
00:13:20,361 --> 00:13:22,061
How could I not come running?

221
00:13:22,261 --> 00:13:24,731
And what about you? You hugged me
so tight because you were scared.

222
00:13:25,831 --> 00:13:29,001
Are you okay? Are you hurt?
It's okay.

223
00:13:30,771 --> 00:13:31,771
It's okay.

224
00:13:32,471 --> 00:13:33,471
It's okay.

225
00:13:38,771 --> 00:13:41,281
Hey, you're the one who hugged me,
Director Yang.

226
00:13:41,341 --> 00:13:43,881
You're the one who clung to me
like a koala, CEO Gong.

227
00:13:45,281 --> 00:13:47,051
Anyway, stop hugging me
all the time.

228
00:13:47,121 --> 00:13:48,781
How many times has it been already?

229
00:13:48,851 --> 00:13:53,091
Unbelievable.
I practically saved your life.

230
00:13:53,161 --> 00:13:55,721
- Least you could do is thank you.
- Thank you.

231
00:13:55,791 --> 00:13:56,791
"Thank you."

232
00:13:57,291 --> 00:14:01,561
- I can't stand you.
- Look who's talking. Gosh, now...

233
00:14:02,531 --> 00:14:04,671
Just drive. My arm still hurts.

234
00:14:04,871 --> 00:14:07,001
You're not even hurt.
Stop being so dramatic.

235
00:14:07,071 --> 00:14:09,141
I'm not exaggerating.
It really hurts.

236
00:14:10,441 --> 00:14:12,871
Gosh, seriously.
Just hold on a second.

237
00:14:15,011 --> 00:14:16,011
Hey, Mom.

238
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:18,751
What? They caught that woman?

239
00:14:19,981 --> 00:14:21,281
That's such a relief.

240
00:14:21,921 --> 00:14:23,621
Right. Okay.

241
00:14:25,191 --> 00:14:26,591
Did they catch that woman?

242
00:14:26,861 --> 00:14:27,891
Yes.

243
00:14:28,721 --> 00:14:30,761
That's great. What a relief.

244
00:14:30,761 --> 00:14:32,761
Now you don't have to be
stressed anymore, right?

245
00:14:39,271 --> 00:14:41,071
We should get going.
We'll be late for our meeting.

246
00:14:41,501 --> 00:14:42,501
Wait...

247
00:14:43,911 --> 00:14:47,081
Postpone the meeting until tomorrow
and go be with your family.

248
00:14:49,611 --> 00:14:51,451
Go on. Okay?

249
00:14:53,151 --> 00:14:54,251
Okay?

250
00:14:55,081 --> 00:14:56,121
Thank you.

251
00:14:56,751 --> 00:14:58,391
Well, I'll be on my way then.

252
00:15:06,631 --> 00:15:08,761
That woman is getting
what she deserves.

253
00:15:09,871 --> 00:15:12,601
It's a huge relief
that she's finally been caught.

254
00:15:12,971 --> 00:15:14,341
You can say that again.

255
00:15:14,941 --> 00:15:17,141
So, have you heard anything else?

256
00:15:17,911 --> 00:15:19,941
No.
The police will take it from here.

257
00:15:20,441 --> 00:15:25,051
I should get Gi Cheol
another Memory Tonic tomorrow.

258
00:15:25,481 --> 00:15:28,351
Father, let's go to the hospital
together tomorrow.

259
00:15:28,921 --> 00:15:32,591
- Why? What for?
- For his dermatitis.

260
00:15:33,991 --> 00:15:35,591
I already went
and got some ointment.

261
00:15:36,221 --> 00:15:38,861
- Stay out of it.
- Are you sure that's all you need?

262
00:15:38,861 --> 00:15:40,001
Yes.

263
00:15:40,331 --> 00:15:42,701
I'm going to an event
the day after tomorrow.

264
00:15:42,761 --> 00:15:44,001
It's an overnight trip.

265
00:15:44,531 --> 00:15:47,841
You mean the Geriatric Oriental Medicine
conference?

266
00:15:48,371 --> 00:15:49,501
I'll go with you, Father.

267
00:15:49,911 --> 00:15:52,311
- No, I'm fine.
- You should go together.

268
00:15:52,371 --> 00:15:54,841
I said it's fine. It's not far.
I'm more comfortable going alone.

269
00:16:05,991 --> 00:16:07,921
Hey, Hyun Bin.

270
00:16:09,691 --> 00:16:10,861
Oh my...

271
00:16:12,531 --> 00:16:15,901
Father, look.
Hyun Bin won't listen to me at all.

272
00:16:16,971 --> 00:16:19,871
Why won't you get married?

273
00:16:21,701 --> 00:16:23,041
Is it because you
still can't get over...

274
00:16:23,111 --> 00:16:24,111
Gi Cheol's granddaughter?

275
00:16:24,741 --> 00:16:28,511
- Not this again.
- You get over people with people.

276
00:16:29,211 --> 00:16:30,281
I'm going upstairs.

277
00:16:32,181 --> 00:16:33,181
Hey.

278
00:16:35,221 --> 00:16:36,791
You see, Father?

279
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,791
Just push forward.
Do whatever it takes.

280
00:16:39,321 --> 00:16:42,191
- Father.
- Just do it.

281
00:16:44,261 --> 00:16:48,901
By the way, Father, Se Ri's business
is doing great lately.

282
00:16:49,631 --> 00:16:51,001
Of course it is.

283
00:16:51,631 --> 00:16:52,731
Oh, that's right.

284
00:16:52,731 --> 00:16:56,171
My store might be selected
as an Excellent Store this time.

285
00:16:56,441 --> 00:16:57,471
Really?

286
00:16:58,211 --> 00:17:00,711
Wow, then it'll do even better
than before.

287
00:17:01,081 --> 00:17:04,181
That's our amazing Cha Se Ri. Right?

288
00:17:04,381 --> 00:17:06,151
And you, make sure you get
the nomination this time,

289
00:17:06,551 --> 00:17:08,451
and win your city council seat.

290
00:17:09,251 --> 00:17:10,891
That's easier said than done.

291
00:17:11,151 --> 00:17:14,761
Honey, everything's going smoothly.
What are you worried about?

292
00:17:14,861 --> 00:17:17,091
I'll do everything I can to help,
so don't you worry.

293
00:17:17,961 --> 00:17:19,331
In any case,
all of you need to hurry.

294
00:17:20,301 --> 00:17:21,831
Se Ri, hurry up
and get Hyun Bin married.

295
00:17:21,831 --> 00:17:23,531
And you,
make something of yourself quickly.

296
00:17:24,101 --> 00:17:26,131
I'm running out of time.

297
00:17:27,371 --> 00:17:28,741
What? What do you mean,
you're running out of time?

298
00:17:30,471 --> 00:17:32,871
I'm so old,
it wouldn't be surprising...

299
00:17:32,941 --> 00:17:34,911
if something happened
to me tomorrow.

300
00:17:35,141 --> 00:17:37,981
Oh, Father,
please don't say things like that.

301
00:17:37,981 --> 00:17:39,711
People live
until they're 100 these days.

302
00:17:48,391 --> 00:17:51,091
Oh my, no way.
Grandfather caught her himself?

303
00:17:51,991 --> 00:17:53,931
That woman was
totally out of control.

304
00:17:54,101 --> 00:17:56,731
He didn't use brute force,
he used his brain. See?

305
00:17:57,071 --> 00:17:58,431
He said he tricked
her so cleverly...

306
00:17:58,501 --> 00:18:00,071
that he even got
a confession out of her.

307
00:18:00,241 --> 00:18:02,101
Even the police were
completely stunned.

308
00:18:03,741 --> 00:18:05,811
Grandfather's memory
hasn't returned,

309
00:18:05,871 --> 00:18:08,041
but it looks like
his old spirit is back.

310
00:18:08,441 --> 00:18:11,351
Yes. But Ju Ah, are you okay?

311
00:18:11,581 --> 00:18:14,521
Little noise startles me,
but I'm fine.

312
00:18:14,951 --> 00:18:18,191
But why would that woman
do something so horrible?

313
00:18:18,821 --> 00:18:23,021
She couldn't accept the fact
that she'd killed her own brother.

314
00:18:23,891 --> 00:18:26,191
I think she used Father,
with his memory loss,

315
00:18:26,261 --> 00:18:28,131
as a substitute
for her dead brother.

316
00:18:37,511 --> 00:18:39,471
What if something
had happened to you?

317
00:18:39,541 --> 00:18:40,641
You were so reckless.

318
00:18:42,211 --> 00:18:47,181
Jo Mun Sik is the coward.
I'm Gong Gi Cheol.

319
00:18:50,121 --> 00:18:51,121
Why?

320
00:18:51,991 --> 00:18:54,761
Don't you feel relieved now that
Jo Mi Hyang's been caught?

321
00:18:55,561 --> 00:18:57,231
Where do I go back to...

322
00:18:58,161 --> 00:19:01,431
to get the last 30 years back?

323
00:19:02,161 --> 00:19:03,701
I'm just wondering.

324
00:19:04,701 --> 00:19:07,671
Are you always so full
of pointless thoughts?

325
00:19:08,971 --> 00:19:09,971
What did you say?

326
00:19:11,571 --> 00:19:14,681
Well, you're saying things
that don't matter.

327
00:19:16,081 --> 00:19:18,051
Look, I came back, didn't I?

328
00:19:18,911 --> 00:19:21,681
Let's stop looking back
and only look forward.

329
00:19:23,951 --> 00:19:24,951
All right.

330
00:19:26,591 --> 00:19:27,761
I'm going to bed.

331
00:19:39,801 --> 00:19:40,941
Why are you following me?

332
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:42,671
Mom, you're hurting, aren't you?

333
00:19:43,201 --> 00:19:44,241
What?

334
00:19:44,911 --> 00:19:45,971
Oh, me?

335
00:19:46,511 --> 00:19:49,541
The radiation therapy
must have been rough today.

336
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:52,881
Does it hurt on the surface,
or on the inside?

337
00:19:53,551 --> 00:19:56,751
- Both.
- Hold on. I'll go get a cold pack.

338
00:19:57,991 --> 00:19:59,691
Get it without your dad
and Uncle seeing.

339
00:20:00,161 --> 00:20:01,191
Why?

340
00:20:01,521 --> 00:20:04,491
Mom, why do you always hide it
when you're struggling?

341
00:20:04,761 --> 00:20:06,731
It makes me uncomfortable.

342
00:20:07,161 --> 00:20:10,271
I hate making the family
worry about me.

343
00:20:11,101 --> 00:20:12,171
Seriously.

344
00:20:12,231 --> 00:20:14,301
Your dad is worried
about Grandfather,

345
00:20:14,371 --> 00:20:18,011
and your uncle is a newlywed.
Just keep it quiet. All right?

346
00:20:21,341 --> 00:20:22,911
- It stings.
- Goodness...

347
00:20:25,181 --> 00:20:29,321
Oh, this is killing me.
Hey, your sister in dying.

348
00:20:29,381 --> 00:20:31,821
Oh, your poor sister is dying.

349
00:20:31,891 --> 00:20:34,021
What have you been doing
out so late?

350
00:20:34,721 --> 00:20:37,031
- I was working.
- Working?

351
00:20:37,591 --> 00:20:39,661
Aren't you working part time
at Mother's store?

352
00:20:41,301 --> 00:20:46,131
How can my only brother be
so uninterested in his own sister?

353
00:20:50,641 --> 00:20:52,071
Aren't you even going to ask
what I do?

354
00:20:52,341 --> 00:20:53,811
I'm not curious.

355
00:20:55,081 --> 00:20:58,451
- Why are you going in there?
- Ji Hu isn't back yet.

356
00:21:01,881 --> 00:21:04,851
My one and only brother.
I can't believe him.

357
00:21:05,391 --> 00:21:08,261
Times like these,
I wish Min Seo was here.

358
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:09,791
Honey.

359
00:21:11,361 --> 00:21:12,391
Well...

360
00:21:12,631 --> 00:21:14,331
I thought I heard your brother.

361
00:21:18,231 --> 00:21:19,401
Have some of this.

362
00:21:20,201 --> 00:21:22,541
You're the best, Mom.

363
00:21:23,411 --> 00:21:26,211
Work must be busy.
You're getting home so late.

364
00:21:26,541 --> 00:21:28,741
But it's really fun.

365
00:21:30,881 --> 00:21:32,351
But Eun Bin,

366
00:21:32,651 --> 00:21:35,051
do you know what
your brother's type is?

367
00:21:35,451 --> 00:21:38,491
Not this again.
Do you want to see him go berserk?

368
00:21:38,551 --> 00:21:41,361
What can I do?
Grandfather is being so pushy.

369
00:21:41,921 --> 00:21:44,691
You scared me. Hey, Hyun Bin.

370
00:21:45,331 --> 00:21:46,331
I've made myself clear.

371
00:21:46,391 --> 00:21:47,761
I have no intention
of getting married.

372
00:21:48,061 --> 00:21:49,261
Hyun Bin, don't be like that.

373
00:21:49,331 --> 00:21:51,371
Let's just sign you up
for a matchmaking agency.

374
00:21:51,531 --> 00:21:55,741
- You never know.
- No. I already warned you.

375
00:21:58,841 --> 00:22:00,281
Honestly.

376
00:22:02,381 --> 00:22:03,551
Mom, just give up.

377
00:22:03,611 --> 00:22:06,081
He's only ever had eyes
for Gong Ju Ah.

378
00:22:06,151 --> 00:22:07,681
He's a total solo man.

379
00:22:08,321 --> 00:22:10,551
What in the world is so charming
about that brat?

380
00:22:10,891 --> 00:22:13,521
It'd be easier
to convince Grandfather.

381
00:22:14,491 --> 00:22:17,531
What am I going to do?
Gosh, I don't know.

382
00:22:17,591 --> 00:22:18,961
Honestly.

383
00:22:21,761 --> 00:22:24,371
You need to get
a bone marrow test right away.

384
00:22:24,731 --> 00:22:26,371
Tell your family,

385
00:22:26,371 --> 00:22:27,801
and get admitted to the hospital
right away.

386
00:22:39,111 --> 00:22:43,281
I'll have the cheeseburger combo.

387
00:22:43,721 --> 00:22:44,821
What are you getting?

388
00:22:45,751 --> 00:22:47,661
I'll have the garlic shrimp burger,

389
00:22:47,721 --> 00:22:50,061
with an extra patty
and a slice of cheese.

390
00:22:50,391 --> 00:22:53,731
Swap the fries for crispy tenders,
and for the drink...

391
00:22:53,801 --> 00:22:56,301
Oh, the low sugar apple juice,
and a corn salad for the side.

392
00:22:56,361 --> 00:22:57,771
I didn't catch that. Say it again.

393
00:22:58,031 --> 00:23:01,571
The garlic shrimp burger with...

394
00:23:01,641 --> 00:23:04,671
- an extra patty and a cheese slice.
- Again, again.

395
00:23:04,741 --> 00:23:08,681
- Gosh, you heard me.
- Add a cheeseburger combo.

396
00:23:09,981 --> 00:23:13,821
- Seriously, why did you even ask?
- Please pay.

397
00:23:15,851 --> 00:23:17,251
Gosh.

398
00:23:25,631 --> 00:23:29,261
Seriously.
Are you dropping food everywhere?

399
00:23:30,701 --> 00:23:33,541
You're so fussy.
Fine, then you drive.

400
00:23:33,601 --> 00:23:35,641
Hey, my arm hurts, you know?

401
00:23:36,701 --> 00:23:39,441
- You're holding your burgers fine.
- Gosh, I seriously...

402
00:23:39,511 --> 00:23:42,141
I really hate it when people
spill things in my car.

403
00:23:42,781 --> 00:23:44,181
Gosh, I really hate this.

404
00:23:52,521 --> 00:23:55,321
- Can I have some fries?
- Don't you have hands?

405
00:23:55,391 --> 00:23:57,261
One hand's on my burger,
the other's on the wheel.

406
00:23:57,261 --> 00:23:59,031
I don't have a free hand.

407
00:24:00,961 --> 00:24:03,261
- Here.
- Ketchup.

408
00:24:12,811 --> 00:24:14,881
- I'm thirsty.
- What?

409
00:24:23,451 --> 00:24:25,551
Hey, what are you doing?
Why are you sticking your mouth out?

410
00:24:25,921 --> 00:24:26,991
Wipe it off.

411
00:24:27,321 --> 00:24:30,761
Hey, what are you imagining?
Hurry up.

412
00:24:32,731 --> 00:24:34,561
Gosh, you're so annoying.

413
00:24:37,301 --> 00:24:39,071
Oh. Right, right.

414
00:24:45,741 --> 00:24:48,841
Hey! What are you doing?

415
00:24:48,911 --> 00:24:50,351
Gosh, why would you
put this on the car?

416
00:24:50,411 --> 00:24:52,611
- Seriously, what are you...
- There's one over there too.

417
00:24:53,681 --> 00:24:55,851
- Oh no. My bad.
- This is...

418
00:25:05,091 --> 00:25:07,501
Everything looks good,
but since it's a new brand,

419
00:25:07,561 --> 00:25:08,901
initial recognition is low.

420
00:25:09,361 --> 00:25:11,531
I'm concerned you won't be able
to achieve...

421
00:25:11,601 --> 00:25:13,401
the sales target in your proposal.

422
00:25:13,501 --> 00:25:15,471
Oh, you don't need
to worry about that.

423
00:25:16,041 --> 00:25:18,211
It's still confidential,
so I can't tell you the details,

424
00:25:18,271 --> 00:25:20,411
but we're discussing a sponsorship
with a top stylist team,

425
00:25:20,481 --> 00:25:22,241
and the talks are going very well.

426
00:25:22,611 --> 00:25:24,511
Really? Which one?

427
00:25:25,581 --> 00:25:26,981
That's a secret.

428
00:25:30,451 --> 00:25:33,121
And don't worry about
production stability either.

429
00:25:33,291 --> 00:25:36,591
We have a stable production line
ready to meet demand.

430
00:25:37,831 --> 00:25:40,861
Our goal isn't just to get
our products in your store.

431
00:25:41,031 --> 00:25:43,871
Our goal is to become a bestselling brand
at Catch and Top.

432
00:25:44,231 --> 00:25:47,341
I'm confident that consumers
will recognize the value...

433
00:25:47,441 --> 00:25:50,101
of the clothes CEO Gong creates.

434
00:25:58,081 --> 00:25:59,651
Let's move forward
with the contract.

435
00:26:03,451 --> 00:26:06,991
- Thank you for deciding quickly.
- I look forward to it.

436
00:26:10,121 --> 00:26:12,191
(Meeting Room)

437
00:26:23,101 --> 00:26:24,811
Well, let's at least high five.

438
00:26:26,371 --> 00:26:28,011
Gosh, so annoying.

439
00:26:29,411 --> 00:26:30,551
By the way, what was that...

440
00:26:30,611 --> 00:26:32,781
about a sponsorship with
the top stylist team?

441
00:26:33,011 --> 00:26:34,551
We haven't even looked
into sponsorships.

442
00:26:34,621 --> 00:26:35,681
Why would you lie like that?

443
00:26:36,681 --> 00:26:39,091
We just have to turn
that bluff into reality.

444
00:26:39,391 --> 00:26:40,691
Just trust me.

445
00:26:53,771 --> 00:26:56,101
Here. Starting today,

446
00:26:56,171 --> 00:26:57,171
you two are in charge
of this location.

447
00:26:57,241 --> 00:26:58,711
What? Ma'am...

448
00:26:58,841 --> 00:27:03,281
Make sure you take today's outfits
and the spares. I'm leaving.

449
00:27:03,341 --> 00:27:04,951
Take care, ma'am.

450
00:27:06,311 --> 00:27:09,981
This is unbelievable.
She can't function without her.

451
00:27:10,751 --> 00:27:14,191
- Why? Who is it?
- Lee Yoon Seo.

452
00:27:14,661 --> 00:27:16,961
Lee Yoon Seo?
The actress Lee Yoon Seo?

453
00:27:16,961 --> 00:27:18,731
I like her so much.

454
00:27:20,761 --> 00:27:22,001
Hold on to that feeling.

455
00:27:34,081 --> 00:27:36,911
Goodness,
I can't memorize these lines.

456
00:27:37,711 --> 00:27:40,821
Gosh, you messed up my whole routine.
Now my mood is shot.

457
00:27:41,121 --> 00:27:42,581
I'm sorry I'm late.

458
00:27:42,851 --> 00:27:45,521
How many times have I told you
to leave early in case of traffic?

459
00:27:45,691 --> 00:27:47,121
But this is the first time
I've been late.

460
00:27:48,761 --> 00:27:51,361
- I'm sorry.
- Goodness.

461
00:28:02,701 --> 00:28:05,111
- It won't go in.
- Hey, kid, the shoehorn. Quick.

462
00:28:05,271 --> 00:28:06,271
Yes.

463
00:28:08,611 --> 00:28:11,151
I said the shoe won't go on.

464
00:28:15,721 --> 00:28:17,921
Just try to put it on.

465
00:28:24,691 --> 00:28:25,761
Gosh.

466
00:28:30,301 --> 00:28:31,301
I mean...

467
00:28:33,401 --> 00:28:34,601
That hurts...

468
00:28:36,341 --> 00:28:37,771
(Always Kind Pharmacy)

469
00:28:40,741 --> 00:28:43,851
- Mother, I'm here.
- Oh, Dong Suk.

470
00:28:44,281 --> 00:28:46,011
Did you come to see Dae Han?

471
00:28:46,481 --> 00:28:49,521
No, I came to see you. Surprise.

472
00:28:50,281 --> 00:28:52,221
I brought you some fruit.

473
00:28:52,751 --> 00:28:56,321
You haven't been looking well,
so I was worried.

474
00:28:56,991 --> 00:28:57,991
You think so?

475
00:28:58,261 --> 00:29:01,931
They caught that woman,
but you're still feeling down?

476
00:29:03,601 --> 00:29:05,701
I know.
I don't know why I'm like this.

477
00:29:07,541 --> 00:29:10,201
Well, I'm sure
I'll feel better soon.

478
00:29:15,281 --> 00:29:19,351
- Medicine from the Ms. Na?
- I'll tell her when she has time.

479
00:29:19,411 --> 00:29:20,411
Check her pulse...

480
00:29:20,481 --> 00:29:22,351
and please prescribe her
something good, Father.

481
00:29:22,521 --> 00:29:24,491
Yes, that's a good idea.

482
00:29:25,121 --> 00:29:28,461
Treat her like your own mother.

483
00:29:29,191 --> 00:29:30,391
I will.

484
00:29:31,561 --> 00:29:34,431
But, I was also wondering...

485
00:29:34,501 --> 00:29:36,161
if I could get some for myself.

486
00:29:36,631 --> 00:29:40,671
- Why? Are you sick?
- No, not that, Father.

487
00:29:40,971 --> 00:29:44,811
- The kind that warms up your belly?
- Your belly?

488
00:29:46,471 --> 00:29:49,211
Well, we're thinking
of trying for a baby.

489
00:29:49,281 --> 00:29:50,681
Is that silly of me?

490
00:29:51,911 --> 00:29:53,281
Yes, that's a wonderful idea.

491
00:29:53,921 --> 00:29:58,551
- Really?
- Have a baby as soon as possible.

492
00:29:58,691 --> 00:30:00,251
I'll make the medicine for you
right now.

493
00:30:00,621 --> 00:30:01,891
Make sure you take it regularly.
Okay?

494
00:30:03,061 --> 00:30:06,291
- Yes, thank you, Father.
- Of course.

495
00:30:06,431 --> 00:30:07,961
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

496
00:30:08,131 --> 00:30:09,131
Oh, Dolphin.

497
00:30:09,431 --> 00:30:10,671
Oh my, Tamin.

498
00:30:13,831 --> 00:30:15,641
Wow, what a coincidence.
I just saw you this morning.

499
00:30:15,701 --> 00:30:16,741
It's so good to see you again.

500
00:30:17,071 --> 00:30:18,071
You too.

501
00:30:18,741 --> 00:30:20,411
But what are you doing
at the clinic?

502
00:30:21,241 --> 00:30:22,541
Is everything okay with your father?

503
00:30:23,011 --> 00:30:24,181
Oh, no.

504
00:30:24,551 --> 00:30:26,651
I asked him to prepare some medicine
for your mother.

505
00:30:27,521 --> 00:30:31,421
Oh my, you only do
the sweetest things. Seriously.

506
00:30:32,721 --> 00:30:34,021
I'm heading out to open my shop.

507
00:30:34,221 --> 00:30:35,891
No, stop by the clinic
for a minute before you go.

508
00:30:36,191 --> 00:30:38,991
- Dong Ik is here.
- No, I don't need to see him.

509
00:30:39,331 --> 00:30:42,131
Oh, okay, sure. You go on ahead.
I'll come get you later.

510
00:30:42,201 --> 00:30:43,661
- Okay, see you later.
- Okay.

511
00:30:43,731 --> 00:30:45,631
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye. Watch where you're going.

512
00:30:45,701 --> 00:30:46,901
Watch your step.

513
00:30:47,401 --> 00:30:48,401
Goodbye.

514
00:30:49,141 --> 00:30:52,311
Wow, I heard you
caught that woman yourself?

515
00:30:52,941 --> 00:30:54,011
Yes.

516
00:30:54,311 --> 00:30:56,941
Hey, he's been going all over town
all day, you know?

517
00:30:57,011 --> 00:30:59,451
He's been busy telling everyone
his tale of heroism.

518
00:31:01,021 --> 00:31:02,151
I heard you two are the Chairman...

519
00:31:02,221 --> 00:31:03,521
and Vice Chairman
of the merchants' association?

520
00:31:04,191 --> 00:31:07,661
Yes, you and my father
also used to be...

521
00:31:07,761 --> 00:31:09,261
the Chairman and Vice Chairman.

522
00:31:09,391 --> 00:31:11,961
Oh, that's right. Of course,
I was the Chairman,

523
00:31:12,031 --> 00:31:13,661
and Yang Seon Chul was
the Vice Chairman.

524
00:31:14,701 --> 00:31:15,961
Yes, that's right.

525
00:31:16,931 --> 00:31:18,201
So what's this I hear
about discussing...

526
00:31:18,271 --> 00:31:19,271
how to revitalize the market?

527
00:31:19,631 --> 00:31:21,971
What? He knows about that too?

528
00:31:22,301 --> 00:31:25,311
Well, I told him you used to be
the merchants' association Chairman,

529
00:31:25,371 --> 00:31:27,841
and he's taken a huge interest
in it, you see?

530
00:31:29,011 --> 00:31:33,151
Well, I still don't remember,
but this Onjeong Market started...

531
00:31:33,611 --> 00:31:37,021
- from my father's time, right?
- Yes.

532
00:31:37,121 --> 00:31:40,351
- Yes, we have to protect it.
- Yes, we do.

533
00:31:40,821 --> 00:31:43,391
Hey, have you talked to
Councilor Hwang?

534
00:31:43,891 --> 00:31:44,891
What?

535
00:31:45,231 --> 00:31:48,201
My pledge is to get rid
of Onjeong Market...

536
00:31:48,601 --> 00:31:51,731
and build a landmark in its place
to represent Onjeong.

537
00:31:53,071 --> 00:31:55,041
What, why? You haven't told him yet?

538
00:31:55,441 --> 00:31:58,271
Hey, I thought you two were close,
like brothers?

539
00:31:59,441 --> 00:32:00,941
I will. I'll do it.

540
00:32:01,541 --> 00:32:02,611
I have to.

541
00:32:03,211 --> 00:32:04,711
Don't worry too much. Okay?

542
00:32:05,481 --> 00:32:06,481
Right.

543
00:32:11,021 --> 00:32:13,391
I'm sorry for asking to meet,
Councilor Hwang.

544
00:32:14,091 --> 00:32:15,191
Don't be sorry.

545
00:32:15,561 --> 00:32:17,431
Dr. Yang,
you're a valuable partner...

546
00:32:17,491 --> 00:32:20,261
in my political career.
I'll always make time for you.

547
00:32:22,201 --> 00:32:23,361
What did you want to talk about?

548
00:32:24,231 --> 00:32:25,231
Well, Councilor Hwang.

549
00:32:26,001 --> 00:32:29,871
Have you by any chance considered
changing your pledge?

550
00:32:31,241 --> 00:32:32,741
To the merchants,

551
00:32:33,311 --> 00:32:34,641
this market is their livelihood,

552
00:32:34,711 --> 00:32:36,381
something they've built
over a lifetime.

553
00:32:36,911 --> 00:32:40,011
But tearing it down overnight
to build a landmark...

554
00:32:40,551 --> 00:32:41,621
For them,

555
00:32:41,951 --> 00:32:45,421
is no different from
kicking them out onto the streets.

556
00:32:46,491 --> 00:32:47,791
That's why you, Dr. Yang,

557
00:32:48,021 --> 00:32:51,291
are supposed to find a way
to quell that opposition.

558
00:32:52,961 --> 00:32:56,201
But, Councilor Hwang.
It doesn't have to be a landmark.

559
00:32:56,531 --> 00:33:00,171
We could revitalize the market
and turn it into a local attraction...

560
00:33:02,001 --> 00:33:03,971
If you're going to be this soft,
Dr. Yang,

561
00:33:04,341 --> 00:33:06,641
I can't back you for the nomination.

562
00:33:10,541 --> 00:33:11,751
Should I find someone else?

563
00:33:15,451 --> 00:33:17,751
What do you mean it's not easy,
Councilor Hwang?

564
00:33:18,821 --> 00:33:20,021
If you put it that way,

565
00:33:20,421 --> 00:33:22,791
then we'll have no choice
but to consider other sites.

566
00:33:23,761 --> 00:33:26,691
There's no time.
Please wrap this up quickly.

567
00:33:27,161 --> 00:33:28,631
Yes, I'll be waiting.

568
00:33:28,731 --> 00:33:32,531
(Taehan Group)

569
00:33:32,671 --> 00:33:33,671
Director Baek,

570
00:33:34,301 --> 00:33:36,441
is there a problem
with Onjeong Market?

571
00:33:36,841 --> 00:33:38,771
Looks like there's some trouble.

572
00:33:39,111 --> 00:33:40,811
Well, we'll just have to
wait and see.

573
00:33:41,011 --> 00:33:44,481
Is the FG sale proceeding
without any issues?

574
00:33:44,711 --> 00:33:46,711
Yes, Executive Director Hwangbo
is currently...

575
00:33:46,781 --> 00:33:48,521
in final negotiations
with the buyer.

576
00:33:48,821 --> 00:33:50,721
And has the Fashion Division office
been cleared out?

577
00:33:50,991 --> 00:33:52,551
Yes, they say
Brand Business Division...

578
00:33:52,621 --> 00:33:53,621
is scheduled to move in.

579
00:33:56,591 --> 00:33:57,631
Executive Director Hwangbo.

580
00:33:59,061 --> 00:34:01,531
I thought he had some ambition,
but he just does as he's told.

581
00:34:02,031 --> 00:34:03,561
He has the mentality of a servant,
down to his bones.

582
00:34:04,871 --> 00:34:06,601
Maybe that's why.
He's out of the office today,

583
00:34:06,671 --> 00:34:08,541
saying he's tracking
the Vice President's schedule.

584
00:34:10,871 --> 00:34:13,111
The way he doesn't even dream
of being in charge,

585
00:34:14,211 --> 00:34:16,311
shows you can't fight your nature.

586
00:34:17,011 --> 00:34:21,681
(Cabinetry Factory)

587
00:34:36,331 --> 00:34:37,501
Surprise.

588
00:34:38,631 --> 00:34:39,731
Surprise.

589
00:34:40,371 --> 00:34:42,041
- Oh my, this is amazing.
- What's all this, Vice President?

590
00:34:42,101 --> 00:34:44,741
- I haven't had this in forever.
- No way, is this it?

591
00:34:44,811 --> 00:34:46,941
- I bought every kind there is.
- Let's pass them around.

592
00:34:47,011 --> 00:34:48,611
Okay, here you go.

593
00:34:48,681 --> 00:34:50,481
- This looks delicious.
- It looks so good.

594
00:34:53,011 --> 00:34:55,281
- Hey, who did that?
- Thanks for the food.

595
00:34:55,351 --> 00:34:58,391
- Seriously, stop hitting me.
- Why are you here spying?

596
00:34:58,451 --> 00:35:00,821
You've become
Director Baek's stooge.

597
00:35:01,621 --> 00:35:05,331
- Hey, are you calling me a dog?
- Woof, woof.

598
00:35:07,831 --> 00:35:10,031
So that's why my ears were burning.

599
00:35:10,431 --> 00:35:12,501
You little brat,
were you following me again?

600
00:35:12,931 --> 00:35:13,931
No...

601
00:35:14,001 --> 00:35:15,671
Wasn't selling off FG
enough for you?

602
00:35:15,741 --> 00:35:17,371
What are you trying to pull now?

603
00:35:17,441 --> 00:35:18,841
That hurts.

604
00:35:20,841 --> 00:35:22,511
Why is this guy here?

605
00:35:23,681 --> 00:35:25,851
- Oh my.
- You little...

606
00:35:26,911 --> 00:35:28,251
Long time no see, everyone...

607
00:35:28,681 --> 00:35:31,551
- It's good to see you.
- Well, we're not happy to see you.

608
00:35:32,151 --> 00:35:35,291
You have no shame.
How dare you show your face here?

609
00:35:35,621 --> 00:35:36,621
Traitor.

610
00:35:37,021 --> 00:35:38,261
Turncoat.

611
00:35:39,391 --> 00:35:43,631
Come on, you're all being too harsh.
After all we've been through.

612
00:35:43,701 --> 00:35:45,801
So shameless.
Playing the sympathy card?

613
00:35:45,871 --> 00:35:46,871
Get out of here.

614
00:35:47,571 --> 00:35:49,641
- Goodness.
- Get lost, you traitor.

615
00:35:49,871 --> 00:35:51,041
- Gosh.
- Get lost.

616
00:35:51,111 --> 00:35:52,511
- Leave.
- Get lost.

617
00:35:52,741 --> 00:35:53,741
What are you doing here?

618
00:35:53,811 --> 00:35:55,211
Director Yang, what are you doing?
Help me out here.

619
00:35:55,281 --> 00:35:56,811
And why would I do that?

620
00:35:57,751 --> 00:35:58,981
Seriously?
You're really going to be like this?

621
00:36:01,021 --> 00:36:03,021
All right, let's head inside.

622
00:36:03,981 --> 00:36:05,821
- Gosh, goodness.
- Be gone.

623
00:36:05,891 --> 00:36:06,891
Get lost.

624
00:36:15,161 --> 00:36:16,161
(Pelliv)

625
00:36:17,531 --> 00:36:18,531
Unbelievable.

626
00:36:23,941 --> 00:36:25,541
That jerk.

627
00:36:27,111 --> 00:36:30,311
All right, everyone, don't mind him.
Let's focus on work.

628
00:36:30,711 --> 00:36:35,251
- How did the meeting go?
- Oh, getting into Catch and Top...

629
00:36:36,381 --> 00:36:37,421
It's confirmed.

630
00:36:39,151 --> 00:36:40,891
- Great work.
- Awesome.

631
00:36:40,961 --> 00:36:41,961
Awesome.

632
00:36:42,291 --> 00:36:43,991
And we're moving forward
with the contract immediately.

633
00:36:44,291 --> 00:36:45,331
In that case,

634
00:36:45,691 --> 00:36:48,131
should we pop some champagne
to celebrate getting in?

635
00:36:48,601 --> 00:36:49,901
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.
We have to hurry.

636
00:36:50,301 --> 00:36:52,231
We have to coordinate
factory production,

637
00:36:52,301 --> 00:36:54,071
and plan our
brand exposure strategy.

638
00:36:54,341 --> 00:36:55,801
And then, we have to
finalize the investment.

639
00:36:56,241 --> 00:36:57,841
And you have to find
that top stylist team...

640
00:36:57,911 --> 00:36:59,071
you lied about having.

641
00:37:01,111 --> 00:37:02,181
What are you talking about?

642
00:37:02,481 --> 00:37:04,381
Turns out, he was
a complete con artist.

643
00:37:04,981 --> 00:37:07,351
What? You don't know the first thing
about marketing.

644
00:37:07,511 --> 00:37:10,181
Look who's talking. You don't know
the first thing about design.

645
00:37:11,951 --> 00:37:13,991
I'm losing interest
watching them argue.

646
00:37:14,721 --> 00:37:15,791
Well, I'm not.

647
00:37:25,831 --> 00:37:29,141
Here are the outfits I picked out
for this week's variety show.

648
00:37:29,571 --> 00:37:30,641
Would you like to take a look?

649
00:37:32,711 --> 00:37:33,741
This is the best you can do?

650
00:37:34,411 --> 00:37:37,781
You asked for
a natural athleisure look,

651
00:37:37,951 --> 00:37:39,951
so I put a lot of thought
into choosing these.

652
00:37:40,681 --> 00:37:41,981
You don't like any of them?

653
00:37:42,581 --> 00:37:43,621
For goodness' sake,

654
00:37:44,451 --> 00:37:46,221
you can't do a single thing right.

655
00:37:51,531 --> 00:37:54,531
Then what kind of style
are you looking for?

656
00:37:55,361 --> 00:37:58,031
Something modern, but also...

657
00:37:58,101 --> 00:38:00,471
a trendy, sporty, casual look?

658
00:38:01,001 --> 00:38:02,241
I see.

659
00:38:06,571 --> 00:38:09,541
Hey, what would you know?

660
00:38:10,281 --> 00:38:13,011
Hearing you say "I see"
just sounds ridiculous.

661
00:38:14,081 --> 00:38:16,081
I'm sorry.

662
00:38:18,721 --> 00:38:20,851
Ms. Lee Yoon Seo,
it's time for rehearsal.

663
00:38:30,131 --> 00:38:31,401
Just stay out of her sight.

664
00:38:32,901 --> 00:38:33,901
Okay.

665
00:38:34,271 --> 00:38:35,471
Go get us some snacks.

666
00:38:36,501 --> 00:38:37,641
Yes, ma'am.

667
00:38:50,581 --> 00:38:51,851
Yes, ma'am.

668
00:38:52,291 --> 00:38:55,291
Yes, I'm on my way.
It suddenly started pouring.

669
00:38:55,791 --> 00:38:58,931
Yes, I'm so sorry.

670
00:39:03,161 --> 00:39:07,971
What? Seriously,
this is just too much.

671
00:39:08,771 --> 00:39:11,771
Hey, 5793! Unbelievable.

672
00:39:12,711 --> 00:39:15,541
Okay, let's mark this problem
and come back to it later...

673
00:39:17,681 --> 00:39:18,881
Ji Hu, I told you
to turn your phone off...

674
00:39:18,951 --> 00:39:19,951
while studying, didn't I?

675
00:39:20,851 --> 00:39:21,851
But it's Eun Bin.

676
00:39:22,951 --> 00:39:24,691
Answer it then.

677
00:39:26,191 --> 00:39:27,191
Hey, Eun Bin.

678
00:39:28,491 --> 00:39:29,491
What?

679
00:39:30,261 --> 00:39:31,961
But I have a test
at the academy today.

680
00:39:34,261 --> 00:39:35,261
I'll call you back.

681
00:39:36,461 --> 00:39:38,701
What is it?
Is something wrong with Eun Bin?

682
00:39:39,931 --> 00:39:40,931
Yes, Father.

683
00:39:42,071 --> 00:39:44,471
You wanted to see me?
Is everything all right?

684
00:39:44,811 --> 00:39:46,911
I need to check your pulse.

685
00:39:47,611 --> 00:39:52,411
- My pulse? What for?
- The sower of the seed...

686
00:39:52,751 --> 00:39:55,281
must be full of vitality.
Give me your wrist.

687
00:39:55,951 --> 00:39:58,391
I don't know what you mean...

688
00:40:01,721 --> 00:40:03,421
Give me a grandchild soon.

689
00:40:04,191 --> 00:40:05,191
Understand?

690
00:40:08,461 --> 00:40:10,501
(Top Seven Ways to Increase
Your Chances of Getting Pregnant)

691
00:40:12,501 --> 00:40:16,071
Ovulation day... Oh, so I have to
download an app like this.

692
00:40:16,641 --> 00:40:17,641
Excuse me.

693
00:40:18,141 --> 00:40:22,441
Yes. Can't believe Woo Jae
had to take his day off today.

694
00:40:22,741 --> 00:40:25,251
- Could you take a look at this?
- This? Yes.

695
00:40:25,311 --> 00:40:26,311
Hurry up.

696
00:40:26,881 --> 00:40:27,921
Wipe this down.

697
00:40:28,251 --> 00:40:30,281
- Okay.
- Hey.

698
00:40:30,921 --> 00:40:32,091
Are you out of your mind?

699
00:40:32,451 --> 00:40:34,491
Did you do this on purpose
to embarrass me?

700
00:40:34,921 --> 00:40:37,991
How could you forget
that one outfit...

701
00:40:39,261 --> 00:40:40,591
I needed for today?

702
00:40:41,401 --> 00:40:43,901
You've ruined
the entire shooting schedule.

703
00:40:44,401 --> 00:40:45,831
Hey, get your boss over here.

704
00:40:46,401 --> 00:40:48,841
I'm so sorry.
It's her first time on set.

705
00:40:49,571 --> 00:40:52,741
You send a rookie to me?
Am I a joke to you?

706
00:40:53,311 --> 00:40:54,711
I said, get your boss.

707
00:40:55,111 --> 00:40:58,351
I'm sorry. But I...

708
00:41:01,581 --> 00:41:03,421
Gosh, this is pathetic.

709
00:41:03,951 --> 00:41:04,951
Hey.

710
00:41:06,121 --> 00:41:09,191
Don't ever show your face
in front of me again.

711
00:41:09,691 --> 00:41:11,831
Got it? Gosh.

712
00:41:18,131 --> 00:41:20,531
You should've told me
the schedule changed beforehand.

713
00:41:20,601 --> 00:41:22,241
I'm so sorry about that. Really.

714
00:41:26,711 --> 00:41:28,781
- Hey.
- Goodness.

715
00:41:30,781 --> 00:41:32,381
Once is not enough.

716
00:41:33,381 --> 00:41:35,281
I have to check twice,
no, three times.

717
00:41:35,921 --> 00:41:38,691
You can do this, Yang Eun Bin.
I can do it.

718
00:41:39,691 --> 00:41:43,421
I don't have to be the best,
I just have to do my best.

719
00:41:44,321 --> 00:41:45,331
Go, Yang Eun Bin.

720
00:41:49,061 --> 00:41:51,271
- Eun Bin.
- Oh, hello in-law.

721
00:41:51,901 --> 00:41:56,171
What brings you here?
I thought Ji Hu was coming.

722
00:41:56,671 --> 00:41:57,801
I just wanted to come.

723
00:42:01,681 --> 00:42:04,581
I must look like a mess, right?

724
00:42:05,681 --> 00:42:07,451
Not at all. This is the coolest...

725
00:42:07,511 --> 00:42:09,681
and most authentic
I've ever seen you.

726
00:42:21,831 --> 00:42:23,401
Why are you so tense?

727
00:42:23,401 --> 00:42:24,901
You look like you're
about to propose.

728
00:42:27,131 --> 00:42:28,141
What?

729
00:42:29,201 --> 00:42:33,811
- So, is dessert not coming?
- Oh, dessert.

730
00:42:34,981 --> 00:42:36,941
Just a moment.

731
00:42:39,181 --> 00:42:40,181
Yes, Chief.

732
00:42:41,181 --> 00:42:44,181
What? Yes, understood.
I'll be right there.

733
00:42:45,151 --> 00:42:47,221
- You're leaving?
- Jin Ah, I'm so sorry.

734
00:42:47,291 --> 00:42:48,291
I'll handle this and be right back,

735
00:42:48,391 --> 00:42:50,091
- so please just wait a moment.
- Wait?

736
00:42:50,161 --> 00:42:51,691
I'll be right back. I promise. Okay?

737
00:42:51,961 --> 00:42:53,431
Go ahead and eat, okay?

738
00:42:59,831 --> 00:43:01,971
Oh, it's okay.
You can leave it here.

739
00:43:06,071 --> 00:43:08,241
Oh. Thank you.

740
00:43:16,621 --> 00:43:18,251
(Will You Marry Me?)

741
00:43:18,351 --> 00:43:19,751
Will you marry me?

742
00:43:21,791 --> 00:43:22,921
Oh, come on.

743
00:43:24,561 --> 00:43:25,561
What's this?

744
00:43:27,261 --> 00:43:30,031
So, is that everything?
Oh, yes, thank you.

745
00:43:30,101 --> 00:43:32,401
- I'll get going, then.
- Hey, Officer Jeong.

746
00:43:33,801 --> 00:43:36,071
- What?
- Where are you going?

747
00:43:36,241 --> 00:43:39,041
Oh, Jin Ah. Hey, I told you to wait.

748
00:43:39,141 --> 00:43:41,981
Until when?
The restaurant is closed now.

749
00:43:42,241 --> 00:43:44,181
What? Oh, really?

750
00:43:45,351 --> 00:43:47,481
Oh, I'm so sorry.

751
00:43:47,811 --> 00:43:48,821
If you're sorry,

752
00:43:49,281 --> 00:43:50,751
tie my shoelace.

753
00:43:51,081 --> 00:43:52,091
Oh, okay.

754
00:43:53,621 --> 00:43:55,721
Wait, but your shoes
don't have laces.

755
00:43:56,061 --> 00:43:58,691
Are you proposing to me right now?

756
00:43:59,561 --> 00:44:00,561
What?

757
00:44:04,831 --> 00:44:05,831
Yes.

758
00:44:07,571 --> 00:44:08,801
My answer is...

759
00:44:13,971 --> 00:44:15,111
Okay!

760
00:44:16,241 --> 00:44:18,211
- Really?
- Yes.

761
00:44:18,281 --> 00:44:19,881
- Really?
- Yes.

762
00:44:19,951 --> 00:44:21,581
- For real?
- Yes, for real.

763
00:44:24,151 --> 00:44:25,491
Oh, Jin Ah.

764
00:44:25,821 --> 00:44:28,491
Oh, my gosh.

765
00:44:32,531 --> 00:44:35,461
- Tamin.
- Yes. You showered?

766
00:44:35,531 --> 00:44:37,261
Yes. Oh, Tamin.

767
00:44:37,331 --> 00:44:40,701
You shouldn't keep your phone
near your stomach.

768
00:44:41,571 --> 00:44:43,041
Why all of a sudden?

769
00:44:43,841 --> 00:44:46,141
Yes, they say it's not good for men.

770
00:44:48,881 --> 00:44:50,041
Without even telling me,

771
00:44:50,941 --> 00:44:52,051
you're trying to have a baby,
aren't you?

772
00:44:53,511 --> 00:44:54,981
Oh, you caught me.

773
00:44:56,021 --> 00:44:57,721
But the doctor said
it would be difficult.

774
00:45:02,721 --> 00:45:04,061
I got tested again,

775
00:45:04,491 --> 00:45:06,061
and they said
it's not entirely impossible.

776
00:45:08,061 --> 00:45:11,471
Dolphin, hey, I'm really okay.

777
00:45:11,931 --> 00:45:15,371
Really. Don't overdo it for my sake.
Please.

778
00:45:15,671 --> 00:45:17,041
I want to.

779
00:45:17,701 --> 00:45:20,871
- What?
- I'm the one who wants a baby.

780
00:45:22,211 --> 00:45:23,341
Oh, really?

781
00:45:25,081 --> 00:45:28,621
I still feel so bad about
how it was with Ji Hu.

782
00:45:29,081 --> 00:45:31,221
When I was pregnant with him,
I cried every day.

783
00:45:32,151 --> 00:45:35,761
- You did?
- Yes. No one was happy about it.

784
00:45:36,261 --> 00:45:37,761
And I had a really hard time too.

785
00:45:38,661 --> 00:45:40,291
If it's at all possible,

786
00:45:41,191 --> 00:45:44,301
I really want to have a baby.
I want to be a happy mother.

787
00:45:45,401 --> 00:45:49,241
I want to give our child
a warm father and a loving family.

788
00:45:50,141 --> 00:45:51,841
Things are tough at home,

789
00:45:51,841 --> 00:45:53,971
and our family doesn't have
much to smile about.

790
00:45:54,041 --> 00:45:56,911
I think if we have a baby,
it will make everyone happy.

791
00:45:58,581 --> 00:45:59,981
Well, I'm sure they would be.

792
00:46:00,881 --> 00:46:04,021
This is what I want.
It's not because of you.

793
00:46:06,121 --> 00:46:07,121
Then...

794
00:46:07,751 --> 00:46:10,661
Can I think about it for a bit?

795
00:46:11,291 --> 00:46:12,291
Of course.

796
00:46:13,131 --> 00:46:14,531
All right.

797
00:46:32,651 --> 00:46:35,121
- Seong Mi.
- Oh, Mother. You're up.

798
00:46:36,081 --> 00:46:38,751
Why are you still up?
Are you feeling sick?

799
00:46:38,751 --> 00:46:40,021
Oh, no.

800
00:46:40,421 --> 00:46:43,121
This area was stinging,
so I put on some cream.

801
00:46:44,361 --> 00:46:45,361
Oh, dear.

802
00:46:47,131 --> 00:46:48,761
Is it because of
the radiation therapy?

803
00:46:49,131 --> 00:46:51,461
Yes.
They say it's a common side effect.

804
00:46:51,461 --> 00:46:52,471
It's nothing to worry about.

805
00:46:53,031 --> 00:46:55,941
Why didn't you ask Jeong Han
to put it on for you?

806
00:46:56,171 --> 00:46:59,741
Oh, I was afraid he'd make a fuss
and worry.

807
00:47:01,241 --> 00:47:02,241
But what about you, Mother?

808
00:47:03,841 --> 00:47:04,841
Well...

809
00:47:06,811 --> 00:47:07,811
What is it?

810
00:47:08,481 --> 00:47:11,721
You're not uncomfortable
sleeping with Father, are you?

811
00:47:12,851 --> 00:47:16,191
Of course, it's uncomfortable.
I've slept alone for 30 years.

812
00:47:17,121 --> 00:47:18,831
Should we get a bigger bed?

813
00:47:20,491 --> 00:47:21,831
So we'd share a bed?

814
00:47:22,001 --> 00:47:25,501
Well, Father can't sleep
on the floor forever.

815
00:47:26,101 --> 00:47:27,801
And you two use separate beds.

816
00:47:30,841 --> 00:47:32,441
Why can't you sleep?

817
00:47:34,641 --> 00:47:36,811
Gosh, I...

818
00:47:37,511 --> 00:47:39,251
I just keep thinking of Jo Mi Hyang.

819
00:47:40,251 --> 00:47:41,411
What about her?

820
00:47:42,121 --> 00:47:43,581
I'm so furious.

821
00:47:45,191 --> 00:47:46,691
Oh, I just want to...

822
00:47:48,461 --> 00:47:49,721
Do you want to kill her?

823
00:47:54,131 --> 00:47:55,601
Gosh, what's wrong with me?

824
00:47:56,031 --> 00:48:00,101
The anger you're feeling, Mother,
is a normal trauma response.

825
00:48:00,631 --> 00:48:03,801
You were deceived by someone
you trusted for 30 years.

826
00:48:04,671 --> 00:48:07,541
If you're angry, it's okay
to let it all out.

827
00:48:08,611 --> 00:48:09,611
Gosh...

828
00:48:10,241 --> 00:48:11,241
Just...

829
00:48:12,151 --> 00:48:15,651
don't let Jo Mi Hyang
ruin the rest of your life.

830
00:48:17,021 --> 00:48:19,491
That's all that woman wants.

831
00:48:21,251 --> 00:48:22,261
I suppose you're right.

832
00:48:23,491 --> 00:48:24,491
Yes.

833
00:48:42,341 --> 00:48:46,651
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

834
00:48:52,651 --> 00:48:55,191
Hey, take a look at this.

835
00:48:55,791 --> 00:48:58,261
These are success stories
of revitalizing traditional markets...

836
00:48:58,321 --> 00:48:59,491
by switching to online sales.

837
00:49:01,291 --> 00:49:02,301
Jeong Han.

838
00:49:03,261 --> 00:49:04,301
I have something to tell you.

839
00:49:04,661 --> 00:49:05,801
What? What is it?

840
00:49:07,101 --> 00:49:08,201
Councilor Hwang...

841
00:49:08,701 --> 00:49:10,341
said if I do what he asks,

842
00:49:10,771 --> 00:49:14,511
- he'll give me the nomination.
- Really? Hey, you have to do it.

843
00:49:14,541 --> 00:49:15,711
You have to do it, whatever it is.

844
00:49:15,781 --> 00:49:17,441
Man, you should be willing
to eat dirt for that.

845
00:49:18,281 --> 00:49:20,911
Yes, if it were just
about eating dirt,

846
00:49:21,411 --> 00:49:23,121
I'd do it ten times over.

847
00:49:23,721 --> 00:49:25,921
Then what?
What is he asking you to do?

848
00:49:26,991 --> 00:49:28,321
He wants to tear down
Onjeong Market.

849
00:49:29,021 --> 00:49:31,621
What? Tear down Onjeong Market?

850
00:49:33,291 --> 00:49:35,331
So what did you say?

851
00:49:36,931 --> 00:49:37,931
Look.

852
00:49:38,701 --> 00:49:40,931
It won't make a difference
if I back out.

853
00:49:41,941 --> 00:49:44,141
He's already in talks
with a construction company...

854
00:49:44,201 --> 00:49:45,211
to build a landmark.

855
00:49:45,971 --> 00:49:47,811
A landmark?

856
00:49:48,911 --> 00:49:50,181
I don't know the details.

857
00:49:51,341 --> 00:49:52,951
But that's...

858
00:49:55,481 --> 00:49:58,051
(Taehan Group,
Onjeong Market Landmark Project)

859
00:50:03,421 --> 00:50:05,661
Sir, Director Yang...

860
00:50:06,061 --> 00:50:08,291
has been meeting with investors
from the fashion industry.

861
00:50:08,501 --> 00:50:10,861
He said he was helping
laid off employees find jobs.

862
00:50:11,031 --> 00:50:13,131
Yes, well, that could be true,

863
00:50:13,601 --> 00:50:16,701
but something about this
seems suspicious.

864
00:50:21,241 --> 00:50:22,581
(Taehan Group)

865
00:50:22,641 --> 00:50:23,641
(Director Baek Won Gyu)

866
00:50:24,011 --> 00:50:27,151
Stop beating around the bush
and get to the point.

867
00:50:27,211 --> 00:50:29,421
Yes. So...

868
00:50:30,781 --> 00:50:32,691
Executive Director Hwangbo
is delaying...

869
00:50:32,751 --> 00:50:34,691
the final approval
for the sale of FG.

870
00:50:36,321 --> 00:50:37,321
What?

871
00:50:41,091 --> 00:50:42,601
Well, well, well.

872
00:50:44,401 --> 00:50:46,901
He said it was all taken care of.
Why hasn't anything changed?

873
00:50:47,471 --> 00:50:50,671
So I checked with
the brand business department,

874
00:50:51,371 --> 00:50:53,011
and they said no instructions
have been given...

875
00:50:53,071 --> 00:50:54,071
about moving the office.

876
00:50:56,381 --> 00:50:59,781
That jerk, Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.
What is he doing?

877
00:51:00,451 --> 00:51:02,721
- Is this it?
- Look at this Pacu Nacho.

878
00:51:02,781 --> 00:51:04,381
- It's really good.
- This is amazing. I love it.

879
00:51:04,451 --> 00:51:06,591
- I think it came out really well.
- This prototype is great too.

880
00:51:06,651 --> 00:51:08,351
- A close up...
- Oh, I love it.

881
00:51:08,421 --> 00:51:09,421
It came out great.

882
00:51:10,121 --> 00:51:11,521
- How about this color and design?
- Which is better?

883
00:51:11,591 --> 00:51:14,661
Are they trying to pull the wool
over my eyes and playing games?

884
00:51:15,561 --> 00:51:19,201
Surely that can't be the case.
Didn't Executive Director Hwangbo...

885
00:51:19,271 --> 00:51:21,171
shut down the fashion division
himself?

886
00:51:21,841 --> 00:51:22,941
No.

887
00:51:23,741 --> 00:51:25,641
Executive Director Hwangbo
was buying time...

888
00:51:25,711 --> 00:51:26,871
for the fashion division.

889
00:51:27,241 --> 00:51:29,481
What? Buying time?

890
00:51:29,641 --> 00:51:32,081
He only pretended
to shut down the fashion division.

891
00:51:32,211 --> 00:51:34,851
He had no intention
of selling FG from the start.

892
00:51:34,911 --> 00:51:35,921
You fool.

893
00:51:37,281 --> 00:51:39,221
Then should I call for
Executive Director Hwangbo right now?

894
00:51:39,791 --> 00:51:40,821
Just leave it.

895
00:51:41,321 --> 00:51:43,261
There's no point in letting him know
that I know.

896
00:51:44,691 --> 00:51:45,731
In that case,

897
00:51:46,431 --> 00:51:47,961
do you think
Executive Director Hwangbo...

898
00:51:48,031 --> 00:51:49,461
planned all this from the beginning?

899
00:51:50,801 --> 00:51:53,031
No, it was someone else.

900
00:51:54,771 --> 00:51:56,671
Unbelievable.

901
00:51:58,501 --> 00:51:59,941
Yang Hyun Bin, that brat.

902
00:52:14,891 --> 00:52:16,491
Come on, what is it?

903
00:52:17,221 --> 00:52:18,991
I thought Jun Hyeok
might be spying on us again.

904
00:52:19,361 --> 00:52:20,391
That fool.

905
00:52:21,391 --> 00:52:24,331
- I know. What a fool.
- He went to all that trouble...

906
00:52:24,401 --> 00:52:26,201
to side with Director Baek
and shut down the fashion division,

907
00:52:26,271 --> 00:52:28,641
and all he does now is
trail and spy on people.

908
00:52:30,341 --> 00:52:32,671
But he won't be tailing us today.

909
00:52:33,441 --> 00:52:34,471
How would you know that?

910
00:52:34,871 --> 00:52:36,741
How could I not?
I see him every morning.

911
00:52:37,281 --> 00:52:39,211
He must have something else
on his plate today.

912
00:52:39,981 --> 00:52:41,581
That's suspicious.

913
00:52:42,981 --> 00:52:45,291
Seriously, what are you hiding?

914
00:52:48,351 --> 00:52:49,461
Yes, Manager.

915
00:52:50,391 --> 00:52:51,891
What? Really?

916
00:52:52,761 --> 00:52:57,001
Okay. Yes, I understand.
Let's grab a meal sometime.

917
00:52:57,161 --> 00:52:58,161
Okay.

918
00:53:03,941 --> 00:53:06,871
Hey, why are you staring again?
Stop it.

919
00:53:07,711 --> 00:53:10,311
It's tiring being this handsome.

920
00:53:11,481 --> 00:53:14,011
Hasn't FG been sold yet?

921
00:53:14,881 --> 00:53:17,381
- Who told you that?
- A manager from a former client.

922
00:53:17,451 --> 00:53:19,791
They said the negotiations
to sell FG fell through.

923
00:53:20,621 --> 00:53:21,751
The due diligence is over,

924
00:53:21,821 --> 00:53:23,691
and negotiations are
in the final stage.

925
00:53:24,191 --> 00:53:25,731
Really? Are you sure?

926
00:53:26,991 --> 00:53:30,461
Forget about FG.
Let's focus on Pelliv.

927
00:53:30,931 --> 00:53:33,431
The factory negotiations are done,
the investor meeting is scheduled,

928
00:53:33,501 --> 00:53:35,131
and we're moving on
to product placements.

929
00:53:36,671 --> 00:53:37,801
Do you have a target in mind?

930
00:53:38,271 --> 00:53:41,911
Labellin, run by Oh Se Rin,
who styles top actors.

931
00:53:43,481 --> 00:53:44,481
Get real.

932
00:53:44,511 --> 00:53:46,411
Do you know what kind of company
Labellin is?

933
00:53:46,511 --> 00:53:48,051
Besides, like you said,

934
00:53:48,111 --> 00:53:50,521
Oh Se Rin only works
with top actors,

935
00:53:50,621 --> 00:53:53,151
so she won't give most brands
the time of day.

936
00:53:53,421 --> 00:53:54,421
Is that so?

937
00:53:55,121 --> 00:53:57,361
No wonder
she hasn't opened my email.

938
00:53:57,791 --> 00:53:59,361
What? An email?

939
00:54:00,131 --> 00:54:01,131
Wait, hold on.

940
00:54:01,191 --> 00:54:03,261
The "brand sense that's ahead
of the curve"...

941
00:54:03,331 --> 00:54:05,371
and the creative marketing skills...

942
00:54:05,431 --> 00:54:07,771
of Brand Director Pacu Nacho Yang...

943
00:54:08,371 --> 00:54:09,801
were just to send an email?

944
00:54:10,171 --> 00:54:13,071
Hey, you don't just barge
into someone's house.

945
00:54:13,141 --> 00:54:14,871
You ring the doorbell first.

946
00:54:14,941 --> 00:54:17,111
Go ahead and try barging in.
See how that works out.

947
00:54:17,611 --> 00:54:18,981
You better come up with a Plan B.

948
00:54:19,281 --> 00:54:22,681
I can't.
I already told Catch and Top...

949
00:54:22,751 --> 00:54:24,051
that I'm working with Oh Se Rin.

950
00:54:25,391 --> 00:54:26,891
Are you actually out of your mind?

951
00:54:27,051 --> 00:54:29,591
You have to set a high goal
to push yourself to the limit.

952
00:54:29,591 --> 00:54:32,691
- That's my secret.
- I'm telling you, it won't work.

953
00:54:32,761 --> 00:54:34,961
Just find someone else
and report it to Catch and Top.

954
00:54:35,031 --> 00:54:37,661
Gosh, you really don't trust me.

955
00:54:37,661 --> 00:54:40,101
If I can land Oh Se Rin,
what will you give me?

956
00:54:40,631 --> 00:54:41,831
Why should I have to
give you anything?

957
00:54:41,901 --> 00:54:44,041
You have to pay the price
for not believing in me.

958
00:54:44,241 --> 00:54:46,811
Fine. Go ahead and try to land her.
I'll do whatever you want.

959
00:54:46,971 --> 00:54:49,211
All right.
If you have so little faith in me,

960
00:54:49,281 --> 00:54:51,511
then let's make a bet on something
you really don't want to do.

961
00:54:52,211 --> 00:54:54,751
I like that idea.
How about a deep kiss?

962
00:54:54,811 --> 00:54:56,021
Something I'd really hate to do.

963
00:54:56,451 --> 00:54:57,481
Seriously?

964
00:54:57,481 --> 00:54:59,151
Why would I want a punishment
for a reward?

965
00:54:59,821 --> 00:55:01,191
You think a deep kiss
is a punishment?

966
00:55:01,191 --> 00:55:04,691
Of course it's a punishment.
And I can't just fail on purpose.

967
00:55:05,121 --> 00:55:06,431
I really shot myself in the foot.

968
00:55:06,731 --> 00:55:09,061
I can't believe this. Seriously.

969
00:55:10,361 --> 00:55:12,871
- Seriously.
- Oh, man.

970
00:55:12,931 --> 00:55:13,931
Gosh, honestly.

971
00:55:14,001 --> 00:55:15,801
(3H Acupressure Bed)

972
00:55:15,871 --> 00:55:18,841
Father, did you get
to the conference okay?

973
00:55:19,111 --> 00:55:21,911
I got here just fine.
Don't worry about me.

974
00:55:22,511 --> 00:55:24,941
You're coming back tomorrow, right?
Should I come and pick you up?

975
00:55:25,141 --> 00:55:26,911
I told you, it's fine.

976
00:55:27,411 --> 00:55:28,451
I'm hanging up.

977
00:55:33,121 --> 00:55:34,291
Mr. Yang Seon Chul.

978
00:55:35,251 --> 00:55:36,921
Let's head to
the bone marrow exam room.

979
00:55:38,091 --> 00:55:39,091
Okay.

980
00:55:44,731 --> 00:55:45,731
It burns.

981
00:55:46,071 --> 00:55:47,101
Are you okay?

982
00:55:48,331 --> 00:55:49,641
I'm not okay.

983
00:55:51,601 --> 00:55:53,041
But what can I do?

984
00:55:53,471 --> 00:55:56,441
At least I'm not getting
chemotherapy.

985
00:55:58,711 --> 00:56:01,351
It's okay. I’m just dry-heaving.

986
00:56:03,021 --> 00:56:06,791
That's because you haven't eaten,
so there's nothing to throw up.

987
00:56:09,161 --> 00:56:13,631
Stop looking so worried.
It makes me feel pathetic.

988
00:56:14,491 --> 00:56:15,761
Okay.

989
00:56:17,631 --> 00:56:19,131
Is everything okay
with Director Yang?

990
00:56:19,931 --> 00:56:22,501
What? What do you mean?
Why are you asking all of a sudden?

991
00:56:22,671 --> 00:56:25,611
Director Yang's mother
was worried about you two.

992
00:56:26,311 --> 00:56:28,411
- That's so annoying.
- Hey...

993
00:56:28,771 --> 00:56:30,411
Keep your voice down.

994
00:56:30,711 --> 00:56:31,881
It really gets on my nerves.

995
00:56:31,941 --> 00:56:33,781
She's always coming by
to spy on the office.

996
00:56:34,211 --> 00:56:35,851
Don't give her any reason
to find fault.

997
00:56:36,781 --> 00:56:40,651
- She's so draining to be around.
- Tell me about it.

998
00:56:41,021 --> 00:56:45,191
Please, let's just avoid
any trouble. I'm too tired for it.

999
00:56:45,731 --> 00:56:47,961
Don't worry.
I'll make sure you don't have to.

1000
00:56:51,761 --> 00:56:53,431
What should I do?

1001
00:56:54,231 --> 00:56:55,601
I feel awful.

1002
00:56:56,271 --> 00:56:59,671
Yes, ma'am.
I'll find it as soon as possible.

1003
00:56:59,741 --> 00:57:00,741
Yes.

1004
00:57:01,011 --> 00:57:04,581
Right. Not as soon as possible,
but right away. Yes.

1005
00:57:09,381 --> 00:57:10,381
Seriously.

1006
00:57:12,991 --> 00:57:14,291
My gosh.

1007
00:57:16,261 --> 00:57:18,821
Why is Oh Se Rin's line always busy?

1008
00:57:20,531 --> 00:57:23,461
- This is making me panic.
- What's wrong?

1009
00:57:24,361 --> 00:57:25,771
The actor I'm working with
rejected...

1010
00:57:25,831 --> 00:57:27,501
all the outfits
for a variety show shoot.

1011
00:57:27,571 --> 00:57:29,401
And the CEO is panicking,
telling me...

1012
00:57:29,471 --> 00:57:31,001
to find alternatives by tomorrow.

1013
00:57:31,801 --> 00:57:35,511
Work hard, and don't talk about
quitting just because it’s hard.

1014
00:57:35,711 --> 00:57:36,881
What do you take me for?

1015
00:57:38,141 --> 00:57:42,051
Hey, do you know
any good sporty casual brands?

1016
00:57:42,521 --> 00:57:46,051
Of course. Gong Ju Ah
just launched her own brand.

1017
00:57:46,591 --> 00:57:49,221
Really? Do they do sponsorships?

1018
00:57:50,191 --> 00:57:53,931
- They don't give them to anyone.
- "Anyone?" What a thing to say.

1019
00:57:54,131 --> 00:57:55,931
No. Anyway,
it's not going to happen.

1020
00:57:55,931 --> 00:57:58,401
I'm already contacting
top-tier people in the industry.

1021
00:57:59,171 --> 00:58:02,071
Excuse me? We're at the top
of our industry, you know.

1022
00:58:02,471 --> 00:58:03,571
Right.

1023
00:58:03,841 --> 00:58:04,871
What?

1024
00:58:08,171 --> 00:58:09,841
Did you find out?

1025
00:58:11,081 --> 00:58:12,351
The employee's contact information?

1026
00:58:13,611 --> 00:58:17,821
At least text me that.
I'll try to call them. Okay.

1027
00:58:19,991 --> 00:58:20,991
An employee?

1028
00:58:23,521 --> 00:58:24,521
There.

1029
00:58:28,191 --> 00:58:29,261
What?

1030
00:58:29,761 --> 00:58:33,801
Gosh, I'm the rookie.
Why do I have to do this stuff?

1031
00:58:34,871 --> 00:58:38,601
The CEO? What is this? Seriously?

1032
00:58:39,911 --> 00:58:41,071
Why are you calling?

1033
00:58:41,141 --> 00:58:43,581
If you have something to say,
just say it.

1034
00:58:45,911 --> 00:58:46,981
What?

1035
00:58:47,251 --> 00:58:49,021
- Yang Eun Bin.
- Seriously.

1036
00:58:49,081 --> 00:58:51,321
The company you work for,
is it Labellin?

1037
00:58:51,381 --> 00:58:52,791
What? How did you know?

1038
00:58:53,091 --> 00:58:56,391
Never mind. Is your CEO's name...

1039
00:58:56,391 --> 00:58:57,521
- Oh Se Rin?
- Oh Se Rin.

1040
00:58:57,521 --> 00:58:58,661
How did you know?

1041
00:58:58,661 --> 00:58:59,661
Eun Bin!

1042
00:58:59,661 --> 00:59:04,161
- Yang Eun Bin.
- What? Are you out of your mind?

1043
00:59:04,431 --> 00:59:06,031
Get away from me!

1044
00:59:11,541 --> 00:59:14,411
What's with the cocky pose?

1045
00:59:18,581 --> 00:59:21,511
Don't tell me you actually landed
CEO Oh Se Rin?

1046
00:59:23,781 --> 00:59:24,981
Of course.

1047
00:59:26,221 --> 00:59:27,291
Incredible.

1048
00:59:27,591 --> 00:59:29,421
- Oh my gosh.
- I did great, right?

1049
00:59:30,521 --> 00:59:31,621
Wait a minute.

1050
00:59:31,621 --> 00:59:34,031
If I can land Oh Se Rin,
what will you give me?

1051
00:59:34,091 --> 00:59:36,801
How about a deep kiss?
Something I'd really hate to do.

1052
00:59:38,161 --> 00:59:41,571
Don't tell me you called me here
just to get a kiss?

1053
00:59:41,631 --> 00:59:43,041
Get a kiss? Please.

1054
00:59:43,101 --> 00:59:45,841
I'm the one kissing you,
as a penalty.

1055
00:59:45,971 --> 00:59:47,811
Oh my gosh,
you must be out of your mind.

1056
00:59:47,941 --> 00:59:49,511
I was joking.

1057
00:59:51,881 --> 00:59:53,481
Didn't you say this is what
you wanted to do least with me?

1058
00:59:54,011 --> 00:59:56,751
Let's just see how much you hate it.

1059
01:00:07,761 --> 01:00:09,601
Don't give her any reason
to find fault.

1060
01:00:09,601 --> 01:00:12,061
She's so draining to be around.

1061
01:00:12,131 --> 01:00:13,971
You two said you had
no feelings for each other.

1062
01:00:13,971 --> 01:00:16,101
So what's this?

1063
01:00:18,371 --> 01:00:20,271
- What...
- Don't come any closer.

1064
01:00:23,981 --> 01:00:24,981
No.

1065
01:00:26,011 --> 01:00:27,381
Absolutely not.

1066
01:00:28,111 --> 01:00:29,121
Got you!

1067
01:00:56,381 --> 01:01:00,181
I made this for you.
I thought it'd suit you.

1068
01:01:01,681 --> 01:01:04,251
My gosh.
Oh, this is adorable, isn't it?

1069
01:01:06,091 --> 01:01:08,521
I'll be praying you find him,
Ms. Na.

1070
01:01:25,841 --> 01:01:26,841
What did you say?

1071
01:01:28,571 --> 01:01:30,511
Yes.

1072
01:01:31,141 --> 01:01:32,241
Okay, I understand.

1073
01:01:32,951 --> 01:01:34,011
Right. Okay.

1074
01:01:35,111 --> 01:01:36,521
What was that call about?

1075
01:01:36,851 --> 01:01:38,251
It's about Jo Mi Hyang.

1076
01:01:38,751 --> 01:01:40,751
Today's the day she's being sent
to the prosecutor's office.

1077
01:01:41,821 --> 01:01:43,791
Apparently, she attempted
self harm last night.

1078
01:01:45,591 --> 01:01:48,161
Why? As if she's done nothing wrong.

1079
01:01:48,361 --> 01:01:51,461
She needs to pay for her crimes.
What's this about self harm?

1080
01:01:51,961 --> 01:01:53,771
She won't get a reduced sentence...

1081
01:01:53,831 --> 01:01:55,201
for diminished capacity, will she?

1082
01:01:55,271 --> 01:01:57,101
This is unbelievable.

1083
01:01:57,171 --> 01:02:00,311
They found Jo Mi Hyang's vehicle,
and inside it...

1084
01:02:02,341 --> 01:02:04,941
- There was a gasoline can.
- What?

1085
01:02:05,081 --> 01:02:06,951
So, does that mean
she was planning...

1086
01:02:07,011 --> 01:02:08,311
to set our house on fire?

1087
01:02:09,181 --> 01:02:11,451
- Mom.
- Mother, are you all right?

1088
01:02:11,521 --> 01:02:12,521
Mother, have some water.

1089
01:02:13,651 --> 01:02:15,721
I'm okay.

1090
01:02:16,191 --> 01:02:18,091
You should rest at home today.

1091
01:02:18,761 --> 01:02:22,291
Please do, Mother.
I'll stay with her.

1092
01:02:39,851 --> 01:02:42,381
Apparently, she attempted
self harm last night.

1093
01:02:42,481 --> 01:02:45,351
She won't get a reduced sentence
for diminished capacity, will she?

1094
01:02:45,581 --> 01:02:46,921
So, does that mean
she was planning...

1095
01:02:46,921 --> 01:02:48,121
to set our house on fire?

1096
01:02:58,661 --> 01:02:59,771
Dolphin.

1097
01:03:00,531 --> 01:03:01,731
How's Mom?

1098
01:03:04,001 --> 01:03:05,541
What? Mom did?

1099
01:03:11,611 --> 01:03:13,651
She said she absolutely has to see
Jo Mi Hyang.

1100
01:03:13,711 --> 01:03:15,281
I couldn't stop her,
so I came along.

1101
01:03:15,511 --> 01:03:17,981
Okay. Hang up for now.

1102
01:03:19,791 --> 01:03:21,251
This is insane.

1103
01:03:22,221 --> 01:03:25,161
Father. Jeong Han.

1104
01:03:26,391 --> 01:03:28,731
Mom went to the police station
to see Jo Mi Hyang.

1105
01:03:29,401 --> 01:03:30,401
What?

1106
01:03:36,601 --> 01:03:38,601
(Holding Cell)

1107
01:03:46,211 --> 01:03:47,451
Jo Mi Hyang.

1108
01:04:36,531 --> 01:04:39,001
(Recipe For Love)

1109
01:04:39,261 --> 01:04:40,871
Who called a board meeting?

1110
01:04:41,131 --> 01:04:42,601
You don't know anything about this?

1111
01:04:42,671 --> 01:04:43,971
This is the first I'm hearing of it.

1112
01:04:45,341 --> 01:04:48,811
She called me pathetic and foolish.

1113
01:04:49,711 --> 01:04:51,711
I'm scared of people now.

1114
01:04:51,781 --> 01:04:55,151
A landmark being built in Onjeong
might not be a bad thing.

1115
01:04:55,311 --> 01:04:56,821
As the Merchants' Association
President,

1116
01:04:56,881 --> 01:04:58,451
aren't you being incredibly
irresponsible?

1117
01:04:58,521 --> 01:05:02,661
- I'm fed up with the vendors.
- Have you decided?

1118
01:05:03,391 --> 01:05:06,331
Just get the nomination
and tear down the market.

1119
01:05:06,891 --> 01:05:08,961
It was your dream
to be a councilman, wasn't it?

1120
01:05:09,661 --> 01:05:13,801
From now on, you're in charge
of taking care of the Yang family.

1121
01:05:13,931 --> 01:05:16,301
- What about you?
- Me?

1122
01:05:18,276 --> 01:05:19,976
Dramaday.me
